org.transitime.avl

Class BatchGtfsRealtimeModule

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.transitime.modules.Module
      • org.transitime.avl.BatchGtfsRealtimeModule
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable

    public class BatchGtfsRealtimeModule
extends Module
    For reading in a batch of GTFS-realtime data and processing it. It only reads a single batch of data, unlike the usual AVL modules that continuously read data. This module was created for the World Bank project so that could determine actual arrival times based on batched GPS data and then output more accurate schedule times for the GTFS stop_times.txt file.

    Note: the URL for the GTFS-realtime feed is obtained in GtfsRealtimeModule from CoreConfig.getGtfsRealtimeURI(). This means it can be set in the config file or as a Java property on the command line.
